Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.
After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later.
If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

DetailedDescription: A Välta Rune allows you to make another player's vote be counted twice tomorrow.
The target will have their faith in democracy shaken by receiving such power and will receive a message about strange dreams.
Holding a Rune will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks.

Description: This armour really is terrible, it's heavy as hell so you won't be able to perform any role actions in the night and it's also full of holes - so it probably doesn't even offer any protection to you from kills. (Spoilers! It doesn't provide any protection at all)

DetailedDescription: Borne out of desperation and/or frustration, you hope this shiv you've been able to fashion will do enough damage...
Using the shiv has a 16% (1 in 6) chance of killing the target and a separate 50% chance of crippling the target
The shiv can only be used once
A Hammer of Desolation can be used to destroy all the items that the target player carries
You cannot use a Hammer of Desolation and another item on the same night
There are some powerful relics that cannot be destroyed, such as the Heart of Fenrir
